```
The name of the sample procedure is `addtax`. It has two parameters, `tax` and `price`, which are both of type `float8`. The caller passes information to the procedure using these parameters. When you call the procedure, it uses the parameter values it receives from the caller in its calculations and returns the result to the caller.

Here's an example of calling the `addtax` procedure with different parameter orderings:
```
declare
    taxPercent float8,
    costField float8;
begin
    // Assign values to parameters
    taxPercent = .12; // 12% tax rate
    costField = 250.00; // Cost of the item

    // Call procedure with different parameter orderings
    result1 = callproc addtax (tax = taxPercent, price = costField);
    result2 = callproc addtax (price = costField, tax = taxPercent);
end;
```
